-- Indonesian Stock Movers: Aneka Tambang, Intiland, Tjiwi Kimia
-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 2012-04-02T09:09:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-02/indonesian-stock-movers-aneka-tambang-intiland-tjiwi-kimia.html
Shares of the following companies
had  unusual  moves in  Indonesian trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the close in Jakarta.  The  Jakarta Composite index  rose 1.1 percent to 4,166.07,
its fifth day of gains in the longest winning streak since a
five-day advance through Oct. 28.  PT Aneka Tambang (ANTM)  , the nation’s second-largest
nickel producer, gained 3.3 percent to 1,860 rupiah, the most
since Jan. 27. Nickel for three-month delivery rose 3.9 percent
to $17,825 a metric ton in  London  on March 30, the steepest
increase since Dec. 5. Nickel was last traded at $17,980 a ton.  PT Intiland Development (DILD)  , a property developer,
fell 1.6 percent to 315 rupiah after reporting its 2011 net
income sank 61 percent from a year earlier to 140 billion rupiah
($15 million).  PT Indo Tambangraya Megah (ITMG)  , an Indonesian unit of
Banpu Pcl, Thailand’s largest coal producer, gained 3.3 percent
to 44,900 rupiah, the highest close since Sept. 9. Indo
Tambangraya expects 2012 coal production to rise to 27 million
tons from 25 million tons in 2011, the company said in a
statement today.  PT Pabrik Kertas Tjiwi Kimia (TKIM)  , a pulp and paper
producer, surged 14 percent to 2,725 rupiah, the steepest
increase since Aug. 18, 2010. The company’s 2011 net income
jumped 51 percent from a year earlier to $70.7 million.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Berni Moestafa in Jakarta at 
